        />

         <AutoActor
        Type="BitmapText"
        Text="- Could not restore Marathon mode"
        Font="Common Normal"
        OnCommand="draworder,1010;horizalign,left;zoom,0.7;x,SCREEN_LEFT+20;y,SCREEN_CENTER_Y-180+(60*3);shadowlength,1;diffuse,#ff0000;diffusealpha,0;linear,1;diffusealpha,1"
        OffCommand="linear,0.3;diffusealpha,0"
        />

        <AutoActor
        Type="BitmapText"
        Text="I'm sorry... But marathon mode is more broken that i initially thought it was. I don't think that many people use Course Mode anymore in NITG V2."
        Font="Common Normal"
        OnCommand="draworder,1010;horizalign,left;zoom,0.5;x,SCREEN_LEFT+20;y,SCREEN_CENTER_Y-155+(60*3);shadowlength,1;diffusealpha,0;linear,1;diffusealpha,1"
        OffCommand="linear,0.3;diffusealpha,0"
        />

        <AutoActor
        Type="BitmapText"
        Text="I know that there are people who still want to use it. But please hang on until the future of SLGJUVM."
        Font="Common Normal"
        OnCommand="draworder,1010;horizalign,left;zoom,0.5;x,SCREEN_LEFT+20;y,SCREEN_CENTER_Y-140+(60*3);shadowlength,1;diffusealpha,0;linear,1;diffusealpha,1"
        OffCommand="linear,0.3;diffusealpha,0"
        />

        <AutoActor
        Type="BitmapText"
        Text="This is the last update of SLGJUVM. I want to start over this project and create something new.::The code currently in the theme has been there since 2016, when I just barely started doing themes for StepMania.::It's 2018, and looking back at it, it makes me dizzy, because of how inefficient and messy it is.::That's why I'm going to restart this project. Maybe with a new name, maybe, I'm not sure.::I can say that i'll stil be using scripts from SL to workaround with this.::::Thanks for almost 2 years of SLGJUVM. It's been fun while it lasted.::I just want to create something new that everyone can use, just like how Simply Love did to the entire ITG community.::I know it will be hard, since Simply Love already satifies all the needs for a ITG player, so it will be hard to get some attention to the theme anyway,::being the fact that i'm planning to make the theme use NITG features as one of it's main points. But we'll see what happens.::If you want to keep up as to what it *could* be, please, go to #themeshare on the UKSRT discord.::I constantly update there on all the themes I work on.::::Thank you for using SLGJUVM, and thanks for making me keep going as a OITG Themer, because initially, when I started creating SLGJUVM,::I thought that nobody would use it, yet, here we are. I can definetly say, that I learned a lot with this theme, but it's not the only place where I learned stuff.::::Being technically ( i think ) the only OITG/NITG Themer by this point, want to thank you. And I hope that you look forward for my future OITG/NITG::Theme projects.::::- Jose_Varela"
        Font="Common Normal"
        OnCommand="draworder,1010;horizalign,left;zoom,0.5;x,SCREEN_LEFT+20;y,SCREEN_CENTER_Y-140+(60*6);shadowlength,1;diffusealpha,0;linear,1;diffusealpha,1"
        OffCommand="linear,0.3;diffusealpha,0"
        />




